apple-calendar (improved)
=========================

This skill is derived from and builds upon the "apple-calendar" skill by tyler6204,
distributed via openclaw / clawhub:

    https://clawskills.sh/skills/tyler6204-apple-calendar
    Install the original:  npx clawhub install apple-calendar

The original provided the AppleScript-based CRUD/search wrappers for macOS
Calendar.app and the `clawdbot` skill metadata, both of which this version retains.
Full credit for the original design and the working AppleScript approach goes to
tyler6204.

Changes in this version
-----------------------
- ISO 8601 date output (round-trips straight back into create/update).
- Optional config/blocklist.txt to fence off calendars: blocked calendars are
  excluded from scans and refused for create/update/delete.
- Past and arbitrary date-range queries: --days N (negatives look back),
  --from / --to.
- Calendar-scoped scans and a --limit option for speed.
- Fixed cal-update.sh: start/end writes are ordered so an event is never
  transiently inverted (no silent -10025 "start must precede end" failure when
  moving an event later), and real save errors are no longer swallowed.
- Expanded SKILL.md: stronger triggering description, macOS Automation-permission
  setup notes, and recurring-event ("whole series") semantics.

